\begin{align*} \frac{\sqrt{507}}{\sqrt{48}} - \frac{\sqrt{175}}{\sqrt{112}} &= \frac{\sqrt{169 \times 3}}{\sqrt{16 \times 3}} - \frac{\sqrt{25 \times 7}}{\sqrt{16 \times 7}}\\ &= \frac{13\sqrt{3}}{4\sqrt{3}} - \frac{5\sqrt{7}}{4\sqrt{7}} \end{align*}

Next, we can cancel out the common factors in the numerator and denominator of each fraction.

\begin{align*} &= \frac{13}{4} - \frac{5}{4}\\ &= \frac{8}{4}\\ &= \boxed{\frac{6}{4}} \end{align*}

